{{Infobox drug | drug_name = | type = combo | component1 = Phenytoin | class1 = [[Sodium channel blocker]] | component2 = Pentobarbital | class2 = [[Barbiturate]] <!-- Clinical data --> | pronounce = | tradename = Beuthanasia-D Special | Drugs.com = | MedlinePlus = | legal_AU = <!-- S2, S3, S4, S5, S6, S7, S8, S9 or Unscheduled--> | legal_AU_comment = | legal_CA = <!-- OTC, Rx-only, Schedule I, II, III, IV, V, VI, VII, VIII --> | legal_UK = <!-- GSL, P, POM, CD, CD Lic, CD POM, CD No Reg POM, CD (Benz) POM, CD (Anab) POM or CD Inv POM --> | legal_US = <!-- OTC / Rx-only / Schedule I, II, III, IV, V --> | legal_UN = <!-- N I, II, III, IV / P I, II, III, IV--> | legal_NZ = <!--Class A, B, C --> | legal_status = | routes_of_administration = [[Intravenous injection]] <!-- Identifiers --> | CAS_number = | ATCvet = yes | ATC_prefix = N51 | ATC_suffix = AA51 | PubChem = | DrugBank = }} '''Phenytoin/pentobarbital''' (trade name '''Beuthanasia-D Special''') is an [[animal drug]] product used for [[animal euthanasia|euthanasia]] of non-food animals, which contains a mixture of [[phenytoin]] and [[pentobarbital]].<ref name="Plumb 2015">{{cite book|last1=Plumb|first1=DC|title=Plumb's Veterinary Drug Handbook|date=2015|publisher=John Wiley & Sons,|isbn=9781118911921|edition=8th|chapter=Euthanasia Agents with Pentobarbital}}</ref> It is administered as an intravenous injection to give animals a quick and humane death.<ref name="Plumb 2015" /> In the US, it is classified by the [[Drug Enforcement Administration]] (DEA) as a [[Controlled_Substances_Act#Schedule_III_controlled_substances|Class III substance]].<ref name="Tighe 2014">{{cite book|editor1-last=Tighe|editor1-first=MM|editor2-last=Brown|editor2-first=M|title=Mosby's Comprehensive Review for Veterinary Technicians|date=2014|publisher=Elsevier Health Sciences|isbn=9780323171397|page=414|edition=4th}}</ref>
[[Generic drug|Generic]]s of this product are also available under the names ''Euthasol'', ''Euthanasia-III'' Solution and ''Somnasol''.<ref name="Plumb 2015" />
