{{Use Australian English|date=January 2018}} {{Use dmy dates|date=January 2018}} {{Infobox book <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Novels or Wikipedia:WikiProject_Books --> | name = Tough Boris | image = Tough Boris.jpg| caption = | author = [[Mem Fox]] | illustrator = Kathryn Brown | country = Australia | language = English | genre = Children's [[picture book]] | published = 1994 ([[Houghton Mifflin Harcourt|HMH Books for Young Readers]]) | media_type = Print ([[hardback]]) | pages = 32 (unpaginated) | isbn = 9780152896126 | oclc = 28257302 }}
'''''Tough Boris''''' is a 1994 Children's picture book by [[Mem Fox]]. It is about a [[pirate]] who grieves when his parrot dies and a boy who helps him through this difficult time.
==Reception== ''[[BookList]]'' wrote "This picture book is full of surprises, both in the simple text and in the dramatic underlying story the pictures tell.", but also stated "the design is confusing; the boy appears on the imprint page but then remains hidden until the middle of the book; some kids may be puzzled about where he comes from."<ref name=buffalo/> The ''[[School Library Journal]]'' called it "A compelling and entertaining tale of adventure."<ref name=buffalo>{{cite web |url=https://www.buffalolib.org/vufind/Record/801313/Reviews |title=Tough Boris |website=Buffalo and Erie County Public Library |accessdate=3 December 2016}}</ref> A ''[[New York Times]]'' review noted "a rather puny story line." and concluded "Resisting the temptation to reveal everything, author and illustrator instead give imaginative children something much better -- a picture book that luxuriates in pure possibility."<ref name=nyt>{{cite news |author=Patricia T. O'Conner |date=11 September 1994 |title=Children's Books |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1994/09/11/books/children-s-books-112909.html |newspaper=The New York Times |access-date=3 December 2016}}</ref>
It has also been reviewed by ''[[Kirkus Reviews]]'',<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kirkusreviews.com/book-reviews/mem-fox/tough-boris/ |title=Tough Boris |date=1 April 1994 |website=Kirkus Reviews |publisher=Kirkus Media LLC |accessdate=3 December 2016}}</ref> ''[[Publishers Weekly]]'',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.publishersweekly.com/978-0-15-201891-7 |title=Tough Boris |date=31 August 1998 |website=Publishers Weekly |publisher=PWxyz LLC|accessdate=3 December 2016}}</ref> and ''[[The Horn Book Magazine]].<ref>{{cite journal |date=May 1994 |title=Tough Boris |url=http://connection.ebscohost.com/c/book-reviews/9405207839/tough-boris |journal=The Horn Book Magazine |publisher=Media Source |volume=70 |issue=3 |page=313 |accessdate=3 December 2016}}</ref>
It appears on the [[American Library Association]]'s 1995 Best List.<ref>{{cite journal |date=April 1995 |title=ALA's 1995 "Best" lists: Notable children's books, 1995: Younger readers |url=http://connection.ebscohost.com/c/book-reviews/9504201484/alas-1995-best-lists-notable-childrens-books-1995-younger-readers |journal=Booklist |publisher=ALA|volume=91 |issue=15 |page=1409 |accessdate=3 December 2016}}</ref>
